## Architecture Summary

When a customer visits a product URL, Shopify uses `templates/product.json` to determine which sections should render on that product page. 

The page-specific output from the template is injected into `layout/theme.liquid` at the `{{ content_for_layout }}` placeholder. In this theme, 
the main product section referenced in `templates/product.json` is `product-information`, which maps to `sections/product-information.liquid`. 

That section contains the Liquid markup responsible for rendering the main product content, including product details, media, pricing, 
and purchase actions. It uses Liquid objects such as `product`, `section`, and `settings` to output dynamic product data and configuration values.
The template also loads a second section, `product-recommendations`, after the main product content based on the order defined in `product.json`. 
 
The {% schema %} block in `sections/product-information.liquid` defines the settings and editor configuration that make the section customizable 
in the Shopify Theme Editor.

